pgTitle: List of ghost towns in Oklahoma

rows.text: Former coal mining town in eastern Oklahoma
Destroyed by fire. Old site 1/2 mile north of new community of Center, Oklahoma.
A logging camp of the Dierks Lumber Company
An oil camp in the Healdton Oil Field.
Originally in Miller County, Arkansas before boundary was redrawn.
Established by Mvskoke Creeks in 1836 part of the Eufaula District of the Creek Nation.
Flooded by construction of Lake Sardis
Post office closed in 1952. Town had a population of 2 in 1977.
